    "body": "fix https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39126\r\n\r\nI misdiagnosed this issue (in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38391) as a race condition, while it actually was that adding extra code made the memory arrangement change perfectly for the bug to not happen.\r\n\r\nThe bug: TSNode:id() returns the underlying c pointer as a string, which may include null bytes; and these null bytes are not handled by string.format in PUC-lua. This resulted in two different nodes being able to have the same id..\r\n\r\nAnd what I mean by not handled is that PUC-lua `('%s'):format('\\0a\\0')` returns `''` and not `'\\0a\\0'` (e.g. treats the string as a c-string(string which ends in null-byte)).",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-16T17:52:21Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39134#discussion_r3094696657"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/39134"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3094696657"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "could still use format() ?\r\n\r\n```suggestion\r\n  ('%s:%s'):format(table.concat({ unpack(node.top.region) }, ':'), tostring(node.node:id()))\r\n```",
            "commit_id": "0cbe066884d28a280d4a8d0c5f6f0acc0a94bea5",
            "created_at": "2026-04-16T16:17:13Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -36,7 +36,7 @@ local M = {}\n --- @param node vim.treesitter.select.node\n --- @return string\n local function node_id(node)\n-  return ('%s:%s'):format(table.concat({ unpack(node.top.region) }, ':'), node.node:id())\n+  return table.concat({ unpack(node.top.region) }, ':') .. ':' .. node.node:id()",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39134#discussion_r3094696657",
